text: T.P. has a formula for his movies and it directly targets an audience of black women.  Whether a comedy or an intense drama like this "Acrimony" pulls at those strings; that fire in the belly anger we all know most black women have that can be exacerbated by offerings like this.  The victim (again) are the brothas who are demonized in most of his scripts to a point where it appears he must either repent or die in the most painful way possible at 'her' hands.  I can appreciate T.P. providing offerings to the Hollywood Gods that provide options for our people's entertainment as an alternative to Transformers 25 or whatever crap Marvel is putting out this week. I just want more than T.P's take on black adult drama AND can a brotha catch a break?!

text: I'll pass on this movie. I'm just sick of seeing stereotypical movies, that show Black men and women in a negative space. Tyler Perry and others alike need a new storyline, this one is old and played out. I need to see more positive roles starring Black people. It's other movie genres, that can be shown with Black people. We are much better than always being at each other's throats. It's time for a change. Instead of always showing us as violent, hurting, poor, using drugs, uneducated, dysfunctional, and etc., we can see a lot of empowering roles, more loving and embracing movies, love comedies, happy families, powerful historical movies, science type of movies, futuristic movies, positive and etc. We are not a one trick pony type of people. Our people are so comfortable and conditioned, to see these types of movies and don't understand how these negative imageries affect us. I believe if we have more positive images of us in film, business, T.V., and other things we will be able to fix our communities and all other things. Not saying images are the only thing that can change our plight, but in today's society a lot of people have become influenced more, by what they see on social media, movies, T.V. shows, and images. So it's a big deal to see more positive images and roles of our people. Look at the movie Black Panther, people/children were more excited about seeing that movie than anything else this year. A lot of people expressed how they felt about seeing that movie. So it makes a huge difference to push a better image of us as a whole.

text: Memo to ALL Liberal-minded feminist Black  women:   This movie is an intense character study of the liberal-minded black woman on film. It shows how a marriage built on lust and not Almighty GOD at the core can turn a fairytale marriage into fatal attraction lightning quick. It's NO surprise that Taraji P. Henson's been specifically cast in this film Acrimony and tv show Empire, to demonstrate the mindset of a mentally and emotionally unstable liberal woman who feels that she's equal to a man. And how she will go to extreme lengths to prove that she's more cutthroat. This film clip trailer is ABSOLUTE confirmation that if we call out every MAN to be accountable for their actions, ALL WOMEN NEED to be held accountable as well.   This film is confirmation that just like Taraji P. Henson's character, all of liberal-minded black women have ZERO ACCOUNTABILITY for your words and actions. And especially when they come from deep-rooted ANGER, the social environment and parental upbringing that you grew up with. I hope this sheds light on the journey that turned Taraji P. Henson's character from peaceful to absolutely ruthless. As a hardworking brotha, I'm not perfect. No one in this world üåé is and that's a fact. But I'm grateful 2 Almighty GOD for life and for helping me be accountable for my words and actions. In my opinion, Taraji P. Henson's character in Acrimony should be a cautionary tale to MEN everywhere that's looking for a long-term partner. WOMEN, this also a cautionary tale for YOU because there's a great deal of masculine energy covering up the feminine energy portrayed by Taraji P. Henson in this film clip. When children are involved, that's where confusion starts to settle in. We need to understand our culture and where we're from in terms of manners, tact, WISDOM and RESPECT in the home and our community as  whole. WOMEN aren't supposed to be operating under masculine energy at all. Women are supposed to be submissive to their husbands and husbands are to be submissive to their wives in the covenant of marriage.   This film touches on 6 subjects: Marriage, Anger, Infidelity, Jealousy, Unforgiveness and Revenge.

text: I respect Tyler Perry and will go see this movie when it drops. To me Taraji P Henson can do no wrong. Empire without Cookie might as well close shop. But my mama is a Author. She's tried numerous times to get in touch with TP with no luck. Even tried to contact Ms. O. She stay praying for a miracle. They be passing up a great Romance Writer. She's even done some acting. She once got a standing ovation for a part she learned in two days now that's talent. I tried supporting her on my Youtube channel. I love my mom and wanted to help her make it. Because she put her dreams aside to raise me. I just wish they would read Petals From The Rose, or somebody who knows these people would. They will be so surprised, SHE CAN WRITE HER ASS OFF! The book is chocked full of stories that should be seen on the big screen or even the little one shid we ain't choosy. Petals was my mama first book, she's written seven all together.  We did Youtube videos for the books but she took them all down. I just wish she at least was given a chance. As far as TP goes, maybe some of you are tired of movies with the strong black woman theme at its core. But Tyler's movies brings abuse to the forefront. I guess  he write about it a lot because he's been there. Let's support these Actors, Actresses, Directors and Producers folks, before we start seeing more and more movies without us again real talk.

I think America is still not used to seeing black people in dramatic roles, well to do families, business owners, intellectuals, all in this movie. He blends thriller, drama, and comedy quite well. The comment about Mel's new boo penis size too small for his tall height is hilarious! text: ü§¶üèæ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è TP just refuses to get talented writers to assist him and I'm starting to think it's out of his own greed. The movie was entertaining as far as his movies go, but so unrealistic.   Alert: Long Spoilers below:  1. Where is Mel's father? And why does Robert's father have to be locked up? Every TP movie lacks a strong father figure. Even in Daddy's Little Girls, the leading male character didn't know who his father was. ü§î  2. Was Mel the only daughter to get money? Why was the house left to her? The other sister was engaged so wouldn‚Äôt it make more sense to leave it to the daughter who is starting a family soon? ü§î  3. Why are they walking in front of a green screen for the park scene? Why is there a bench in the middle of the sidewalk?  ü§î  4. How did Robert grow 10 inches taller in 20 years? Was he a late bloomer? ü§∑üèΩ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è   5. How did Robert go to college on a SCHOLARSHIP if he was a convicted   felon?? Fannie Mae do background checks too . ü§î  6. During the 20 years, why didn't Robert get the felony expunged so he could've gotten a better job?? He had an engineering degree. ü§î  7. Why does the dark skin sister have to have a dark skin husband and the light skin sister have to have a light skin husband? TP loves his colorism...üòî  9. Why is Mel and her BFF still working as office assistants after 20 years? No promotions huh? ü§î  10. When did Mel start smoking?? ü§î  11. Why didn't Mel sue for rights to the name since she added the "Force" part?? A judge may have granted her that ü§∑üèΩ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è  12. Why does TP always show the man's booty but have the women covered u---nevermind...  13. How does Mel even get on the ship?? She was at home during the wedding right? ü§î  14. Why was the pregnacy just glossed over?? That should have been the main reason that drove her crazy and led her to snap since she wasnt able to have his children. ü§î  15. Why does TP think he is still writing For Colored Girls?? That bathroom scene with Diana sitting on the floor was supposed to be poetic but it was just awkward. Diana hasn't seen this man in 20 years yet she knows he's a good man? She's beautiful and ambitious so why is she still single? ü§î  16. Why did the final boat scene read like a cheesy YouTube movie with that amateur suspenseful music when the crew jumped over board ?? üò©  17. Why would Mel just step directly in the chain when most people naturally would have moved it out of the way??  Seems like TP rushed that entire scene. Ok ok so even if TP loved the idea of having her step into her own chain of death, he could've at least had Robert try and save her as she's going down, he's holding on to her on the side of the boat like some Titanic stuff. The new wife comes back alone to help Robert and she hears him telling Mel he loves her, hold on, I got you, I've never stopped loving you, blah blah blah. He tries to pull on the chain but he goes overboard too and due to his injury is not able to swim effectively and he drowns. The new wife looks on in disbelief and is now left to wonder if he only married her to get back at Mel. Just like when they were younger and he chose Mel over her. Just my two cents...  The end.

text: Spoiler. My opinion on this movie. I feel both sides are in the wrong. Melinda  accepted to be his girlfriend since colleges days then accepted to take him back even after he cheated with the other girl. With that came the shatter of of her ovaries meaning no babies for the future due to her rage of running her car into his RV home he was caught in the act in.  Then comes the spending of the 350,000 all mostly on him because she wanted to help him and see him succeed. Robert was very invested in bringing his battery project to life and sometimes your dreams will take years to fulfill as to why it took him 18 years+ to finally get into business with the company. During all these years his wife is the one taking care of the bills and necessities of the home  which he should have also contributed someway despite his criminal record. I'm sure he could have got a job that pays something but  he was too obsessed with his project, even though he loved her. Now with the reunion of this other girl who happens to leave his wallet in his work truck that is discovered by with co working in-laws it puts him in deeper trouble. Melinda will now trust an affair has been going on all these years with THE SAME GIRL. Even with Robert getting the career at the same place this same girl works and giving Melinda  that 10 million dollars and paying her mothers mortgage after their divorce that SHE granted- it isn't enough for Melinda who has invested in this relationship for life. Now with this alleged pregnancy on Robert new wife who is the same girl he cheated with years ago- it drives a barren Melinda over the edge. Everything really comes down to that Robert only used her for two decades while seeing this other woman and finally became successful WITH THIS OTHER WOMAN NOT MELINDA AS HE PROMISED HER OF THEIR RICHES TOGETHER. This can surely drive someone to madness if they cannot control their impulses.   This movie is a lesson on patience and trust and how the lack of those can surely end people up in biggest regrets or in worst cases death.  10/10 for me. Tyler Perry's best work yet.

text: Instead of 10M she should of received half of the 150M. She deserved it, all her young life, money, hard work, working, supporting him, believing in him, going against her family. And then insult her with petty cash,. The other woman saw an opportunity, and like many took the opportunity.  My girlfriend and I watched it together at a conference in a hotel room just chilling.  She was screaming, mad, angry, even got mad at me for my comments, but I could see a lot in this movie going several different ways. But It makes us think into our own marriages , relationships, how far do we go, where do we draw the line. .  I would watch again just to remind myself of many life issues.  Good cast and acting, best of tylers work,  he out did his self , obviously some one he knew experienced some of this and then he embellished  , I am guessing where most of his motivation comes from.  Thanks Tyler for a good movie.

text: I don't understand why people are arguing over who was right and who was wrong because Tyler Perry created full, rounded characters who were like real people with both good and bad sides at one point or another :) sort of like real life! We aren't just good or bad, we allow emotions, situations and other people get the best of us sometimes and other times we rise above it. This movie was brilliant because he portrayed everyone in such a human way. Mel was extremely loyal and supportive but at the same time, weak and a pushover. Robert was sly and extremely self-absorbed but also generous and thoughtful at times. Her sisters were very protective and their husbands very helpful but they were also people with poor boundaries and got involved way too much to the detriment of their sister. This is how real life is! People aren't necessarily good or bad, we are just victims to circumstances and our emotions. How tragic, beautiful and freeing!

text: Yeah, I see the comments about how Tyler Perry does black women a disservice by making these movies about "The Angry Black Women"...yada..yada.  As a creator, writer, director, producer, he is a visionary. His directive is to make movies that will draw big audiences, keep people talking, be entertaining, show different sides of human nature, bring realness (with the exception of some of Madea's over the top antics) to characters and earn a tremendous living. The EXACT thing other movie directors, writers, producers, and creators does.  The phrase: "Hell Hath No Fury Like A Woman Scorned" was not coined by us nor is it particularly regarding us.  Of course, some people will love his movies, while others will hate them. Just like any other movie creator.  All in all, Tyler Perry will keep on keeping on and still maintain his fan base.

text: SPOILER alert!  I would have dubbed him after the cheating period but the way I saw it is that I really understood her mental breakdown I really sympathize with her all the sacrifices she did for him, and let‚Äôs not pretend he didn‚Äôt ask for them like most men when they throw it in your face ‚Äú I didn‚Äôt ask you to ‚Äú because this man did, many times and she did it all over because she loved him it was second nature to her as breathing.    All she ever wanted was for him to get a job and help around because she was so tired after a while the whole battery thing must have taken a toll on her, but even then she never doubted his intelligence she was there from the start. When he got upset that Prescott security asked him to stay away she was clearly distressed for him and felt sad for him, she was there from the start  helping him with supplies and even a name for it. She just wanted to have him help around but what made her stick through and not lose hope  was the promises of her boat her ring and everything he promised. Maybe she was delusional that way just like a child want their favorite toy his promises and words was that little glimpse of hope for her.   Now to see the wallet of a bitch you once saw with your own eyes,  your husband fuck with and cheat with ALONE Is enough to make someone lose it specially when you are already going through an emotional breakdown, and then on top of that Diana was helping Robert and that must have hurt too because Melinda is the one who been helping him the MOST! Diana just happened to work in the same building so her helping him wasn‚Äôt even that hard, if Melinda has the same contacts trust she would have helped him even more! And I feel like Diana she got all the credit but in my opinion Melinda did the most.  And yes she divorced him she was under the influence of her sisters being fed up losing the house but come on how many times do people say something and regret it?? That‚Äôs normal. You can‚Äôt think straight while being distressed. But he didn‚Äôt even fight for her!!!he fought more for his battery than he ever fought for his wife. And the only time he showed remorse was on the divorce day but come on that‚Äôs too late she even said herself he never checked up on her ask her how she‚Äôs doing nothing.   So when she understood he made it she was proud trust me she was in her maniac episode it was too much for her reacting normally cause she was losing it already there and had lost it, but she was truly happy for him. People breakup all the time and get back together but they only broke up once  and when she misses him and wants him back (it‚Äôs not for the success) she finds out that with the WOMAN he cheated with the visual way, already engaged giving her all the things he promised her she‚Äôs pregnant like that hurts and I understand the pain but Melinda was wrong for investing in Robert he was chasing his dream all along she lost her own identity in him after the cheating she should have left his sorry ass and if not after the ten million dollars and house that yeah was generous she should have invested her money in something and moved on as painful as it was but she didn‚Äôt she was clearly sick in a way she sentenced herself to her own misery.  By the way from a woman‚Äôs perspective once you given someone your time your youth your all no amount of money nothings can fix that no money no nothing but the love of the man or self love.

text: Thing about this movie, is not about how crazy she can go.  It's about the time that it took. She believed in him, she spent all the money she could have used for other path of a life she have chosen, for in the end she couldn't just take anymore. Years and years passed and she lost her faith, she was broke, she couldn't take anymore, empty promises, silent treatment, sleeping on the couch, no sex, having her family thinking they can take over her life and what it's hers to decide. And then, a woman that didn't do anything good for this whole years and didn't spent any money at all with him, only brought him to cheat, this time again, comes in just like she is a hero and giving him the dream, out of nowhere from this many years, when the one that worked hard for his dreams, was Melinda. It's sad she waited so long, to the point she couldn't take anymore, but she deserved all this more than the other woman, the woman only seemed like she was trying to steal everything like "you go and deal with that guy and pay him everything", she got the best side of him, while Melinda got the worse side, and not even that other woman probably would have patience and time as Melinda had. I mean, just look around and where was she? Not caring about him. Because she didn't devoted her life to him, she didn't even want to have anything with him after knowing he had a girlfriend. But he also didn't said to Melinda only sorry and left her. He kept pushing and pushing, saying he loves her and that's what make her go crazy. The time he pushes her and in the end, she has nothing left.

text: What baffles me is how fast Robert moved on. He literally got engaged moments after becoming rich. If he really loved her he would've stayed fighting, you don't just throw 18 years away man. He was a good man, but Melinda and Diana were only good enough for him if he could use them to get to the top/be successful. Diana of course left her purse in the truck on purpose because she was lusting after him while watching his videos and she knew how crazy Melinda would get if she knew he was "cheating". She also knew that she had the power to make him become successful, so of course that's what she did and now she's living her best life. Melinda deserved better in life, but out of love she chose to settle for less and sacrifice her future for his dreams. I do believe that Robert did love Melinda, but not as much as she loved him. He gave Diana everything that he had promised Melinda and that is truly heartbreaking. Maybe because Melinda chose to divorce him, his ego got bruised and then he used Diana as a replacement for Melinda, but really he just wished it was Melinda by his side instead. Another thing is that Diana looks younger than Melinda and she is more successful as well and that makes her more attractive than Melinda. Of course that is not Melinda's fault, she was tired and overworked and doing the most for Robert. Truth is men always go where the grass is greener, forgetting that all they had to do was just water the other side a little bit more.

A man is supposed to be the one providing & leading his home & if he's not able to do that for the woman he loves, ultimately there's gonna be a lack of affection from his side & resentment on hers. It was just unfortunate that she filed for a divorce and soon after he got the break she spent years investing in. We also shouldn't overlook the fact that the other woman helped to make the dream a reality (not to the extent as his wife did but she helped nonetheless). This movie is really about accepting the choices we make, even if the consequences will lead to bitterness, heartache & anger. I won't blame her sisters either, they were only protecting her, no one forced her to file for a divorce, that was all her. Despite the fact that she wasn't able to get him back, she needed to accept that it was her choices that caused another woman to reap the benefits of what she sowed. Or we can simply learn to accept that sometimes what's not yours just isn't, afterall, the break didn't come until after she set him free.

text: My 2cents is this was a good movie, even the ending was the best. I am a woman yes, and this thing happens. You love a man and think he will make it one day and he will take you to the top. He did. $10 000 000?  Thing is people want to own others. We came into this world alone and our graves are for one. This is a warning to others to never let your thoughts be consumed over another human being.   We choose what we become. She could have taken a vacation around the world with that $10 million, she never had plans except for being with him. Losing oneself in someone else is never easy.   I watched this last night and im actually taking thought that i should have my dreams, my goals, my joy. When my ex got married within 2 years of our break up, i got in his facebook account. I saw all the messages, the fotos, the vacations, and the nasties. I got into his emails and saw messages he wrote her. I had his passwords, so i had that access.   But i stopped in my tracks. Why was i doing this to me? Why did it bother me? He is an adult and can do whatever he wants with his body his life.

text: So unfortunate. Yes Robert was a selfish douche but she let herself get played. It was over the moment he used her to get a car. She knew it but she didn't want to admit it. And Robert always wanted Diana more, the mild safe option that would unlock all his dreams. I think Robert was a terrible man and Diana is the one missing out by marrying him. It may seem insulting to women, another depiction of a crazy girl who's too dependent on her man, but it's a realistic one. This happens all too often in real life and i can honestly say as a girl I've done the same thing. Borderline harassing and stalking an ex because i couldn't let go, largely due to my mental health issues. I can see why the movie has bad reviews but taraji makes anything work. And i saw lyriq in love jacked, which makes me think he's just got that bad guy face on him. Loved every minute of this movie and it really gave me a better perspective about my own dating life and behavior.
